Nested schemas (expanded):

- target (object)
  - gender: 'all' | 'male' | 'female' | 'custom'
  - customers: ['new' | 'existing' ...]
  - interests: array<string>
  - age_ranges: array<{ min?: number, max?: number }>
  - locations: array<{ radius?: number|null, place_id: string, place_name: string, place_name_parts?: array<{ part_name: string, index_offset: number }> }>
  - document, website_document: optional reserved fields for future first-party audience docs

- ads_details (object)
  - content: array<{ id: string, full_path: string }>
  - details: { ad_cta: string, ad_headline: string|'a$delimiter$b', ad_keywords: string|'a$delimiter$b', ad_punchline: string|'a$delimiter$b', ad_landing_page: url }
  Notes: $delimiter indicates multi-variant strings used for generation/rotation.

- platforms (object)
  - channels: array<'google'|'facebook'|'instagram'|...>
  - channels_formats: array<string> (platform-specific placements/templates)
  - channels_content_formats: array<'text'|'image'|'video'|'carousel'|...>

- campaign_metrics (array<object>)
  - date: 'YYYY-MM-DD'
  - cost: number (platform spend in account currency)
  - clicks: number
  - conversions: number (may be fractional if blended)
  - impressions: number
  - conversion_value: number (currency value for conversions)

Type notes:
- Timestamps are stored with timezone where available.
- Monetary amounts in budget_cents are integer cents; metrics costs are decimal currency from source platforms.
- Some fields may be absent/null depending on channel, goal, and plan (e.g., payment_details, campaign_type_metrics).
- Strings may include marketing copy delimiters for multi-variant generation.
